             Iraqi Prime Minister Nuri al-Maliki
accepted the resignation of Electricity Minister Karim Wahid,
who offered to quit after deadly riots that followed power cuts.
A government spokesman confirmed al-Malikiâ€™s acceptance today in
a telephone interview and said the oil minister may take over
